docs.title: Access Control Lists
docs.description: Ampache supports internal Access Control Lists, these are IP/DNS based restrictions on different actions and interactions with Ampache. By Default Access Controls lists are turned off in Ampache. In order to turn them on you must modify the /config/ampache.cfg.php and set access_control to true

docs.title: API 5 Errors
docs.description: Ampache's API errors are loosely based around the HTTP status codes. All errors are returned in the form of an XML/JSON Document however the string error message provided is translated into the language of the Ampache server in question. All services should only use the code value.
